data.title: Oldenburg Academy Auditorium, Vine Street, Oldenburg, IN
data.meta_description: Built in 1967, this Modern building features a red brick exterior, limestone trim, a limestone base, a front entrance with a large aluminum curtain wall and cantilevered aluminum awning, decorative limestone relief panels on the exterior, and a low-slope roof enclosed by a parapet.  The building is a noncontributing structure in the Oldenburg Historic District, listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1983.
